PN,40402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1784659707
OL,3,CDouble murder accused killed cellmate
OL,4,Cwhile awaiting trial, court told
OL,6,FIn agreed facts read to the jury,
OL,7,FAhmed Hossain KC, prosecuting, said:
OL,8,F"On the 27 March 2026 at Exeter Crown
OL,9,FCourt, James Desborough was convicted
OL,10,Fby a jury of the murder of Steven
OL,11,FKempster.
OL,13,F"On 16 March 2026, which was the first
OL,14,Fday of that trial for the murder of
OL,15,FSteven Kempster, James Desborough
OL,16,Fentered a plea of guilty to
OL,17,Fmanslaughter, which was not accepted
OL,18,Fby the prosecution.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1784659707
OL,3,CDouble murder accused killed cellmate
OL,4,Cwhile awaiting trial, court told
OL,6,F"The facts of this conviction are that
OL,7,Fon 15 September 2025, James Desborough
OL,8,Fmurdered Stephen Kempster (with whom
OL,9,Fhe shared a cell at HMP Exeter, whilst
OL,10,Fon remand for the current allegations)
OL,11,Fby compression of the neck by
OL,12,Fstrangulation."
OL,14,FDesborough is currently on trial
OL,15,Faccused of murdering Claudio Aquilino,
OL,16,F57, and Daniel Coleman, 43, last
OL,17,Fsummer in Cornwall.
OL,19,FIn the agreed facts, the jury was also
OL,20,Ftold about the lives of Daniel Coleman
OL,21,Fand Claudio Aquilino.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1784659707
OL,3,CDouble murder accused killed cellmate
OL,4,Cwhile awaiting trial, court told
OL,6,FThe court was told that both men had
OL,7,Flong-term issues with drugs and
OL,8,Falcohol, had spent time homeless, and
OL,9,Fsuffered from mental health problems,
OL,10,Fincluding depression. Both had
OL,11,Fexpressed thoughts of suicide but
OL,12,Fengaged with services to support those
OL,13,Fissues, jurors were told.
OL,15,FThe court previously heard that
OL,16,FClaudio Aquilino, Daniel Coleman, and
OL,17,Fthe accused James Desborough all met
OL,18,Fwhen they were living at the Sandy
OL,19,FLodge Hotel in Newquay - a place used
OL,20,Ffor emergency housing.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1784659707
OL,3,CDouble murder accused killed cellmate
OL,4,Cwhile awaiting trial, court told
OL,6,FThe jury was shown more than 100
OL,7,Fphotographs of the scene in the woods
OL,8,Fat Sticker where the remains were
OL,9,Fdiscovered, and the cabin where James
OL,10,FDesborough lived.
OL,12,FAmong the photos were images of
OL,13,Fknives, saws, machetes, crowbars, and
OL,14,Faxes found in and around Desborough's
OL,15,Fcabin.
OL,17,FDesborough, of Old Oak Woods, Lower
OL,18,FSticker, Cornwall, denies the murder
OL,19,Fof Daniel Coleman and Claudio Aquilino.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
